NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 26, 1999
Ari Ahonen
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q. How do you feel right now? 
 
 ARI AHONEN: I don't know. I think this is my happiest day in my life. It's party time.  
 
Q. Did you see a lot of National Hockey League games when you were growing up? 
 
 ARI AHONEN: Yeah, yeah. Not on live, but in TV. I watch a lot National Hockey League
games.  
 
Q. Do you know where you're going to play next year?
 
 ARI AHONEN: I play in IFK, Helsinki.  
 
Q. What do you know of the New Jersey Devils?
 
 ARI AHONEN: Not a lot. Just that Martin Brodeur. I like him. Nothing special. 
 
